@node P1 "Editor's Corner"
@toc "menu"

Editor's Corner             by @{"Lori Vinciguerra" link P6}

With the growing interest in using computers in schools, it is clear that
there must be some Amigas being used for educational purposes. Currently,
there is no means of finding other Amiga educators, allowing us to
exchange ideas and talk about new products. This newsletter has been
created to act as a forum for people using their Amigas in schools or at
home for educational purposes.  It will include a discussion section,
interviews, new product announcements, and articles on educational uses
for our machines.  Those of you who are currently using an education
software product are encouraged to write reviews for publication. We
would also like to receive articles about what you are doing with your
Amigas.  This will give others who read the newsletter contacts for
people who may be doing similar projects.

The AEL newsletter will be available electronically for those of you who
have the capability to download it.  I will mail copies to anyone else
who is interested in receiving it.  The current plan is to publish the
newsletter on a quarterly basis in January, April, July, and October.  If
there is significant input the publishing schedule may go to bimonthly.
Initially the cost for subscription will be nothing.  We will try to
remain a free publication unless the distribution list for copying and
mailing becomes large.  Those of you who download the magazine will be
able to maintain a free subscription. The magazine will be available on
any Aminet site and via the OWL Software BBS.

We encourage any inputs for the January 1995 issue be sent to OWL
Software no later than November 15, 1994.  Submissions can be made via
e-mail to owl@davinci.reading.ma.us or via mail to 460 Summer Ave.,
Reading, MA  01867. The success of this newsletter will depend on your
input.  Good luck in your upcoming fall semester projects.

@endnode


